1
00:00:00,940 --> 00:00:03,480
(Episode 62)

2
00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:08,950
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

3
00:00:23,230 --> 00:00:24,700
I hope this isn't a dream.

4
00:00:27,270 --> 00:00:28,500
This really isn't a dream, is it?

5
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:32,640
It's not a dream, Baek Ho.

6
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:39,240
It's really you, isn't it, Jang Mi?

7
00:00:41,150 --> 00:00:42,380
I can't believe it.

8
00:00:43,380 --> 00:00:44,520
I still can't believe it.

9
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:46,750
You can believe it.

10
00:00:47,820 --> 00:00:49,190
It's me. It's Jang Mi.

11
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:53,020
I'm the same Oh Jang Mi who loves you.

12
00:00:55,660 --> 00:00:56,900
Thank you, Jang Mi.

13
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:00,370
Thank you so much, Jang Mi.

14
00:01:24,260 --> 00:01:25,490
About General Manager Kang...

15
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:28,630
Why would he go out of his way
to reveal that he was adopted?

16
00:01:28,830 --> 00:01:30,630
He probably figured that
if I found out he was adopted,

17
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:33,830
I wouldn't accept him as my son-in-law.

18
00:01:33,830 --> 00:01:35,630
That's how he wants to stop this.

19
00:01:36,030 --> 00:01:37,040
General Manager Kang...

20
00:01:37,770 --> 00:01:40,040
looks like he had
a very painful childhood.

21
00:01:41,170 --> 00:01:42,570
He looked so troubled.

22
00:01:43,540 --> 00:01:44,640
It's long overdue,

23
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:46,980
but I'm going to make it all up to him.

24
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:50,420
I'm going to give my son
everything I have.

25
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,590
You can head home.

26
00:01:57,260 --> 00:01:59,420
And one more thing about Jin Hong Ju.

27
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:02,430
- Yes.
- Clear out her desk.

28
00:02:03,730 --> 00:02:07,330
How dare she stab me in the back
and pull a stunt like that?

29
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:11,370
Impersonating Professor Kang,
sending a bouquet with a note.

30
00:02:12,670 --> 00:02:14,570
There's a limit to how much
she can mess with me.

31
00:02:15,270 --> 00:02:17,040
Does she really think
she can get away with that?

32
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:19,440
But I don't think...

33
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:22,250
Team Leader Jin was the one
who wrote the note.

34
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:25,180
Besides, Team Leader Jin never even came
to your office that day.

35
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:28,890
Then who on earth would pull
a clever stunt like that?

36
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:32,360
Who? Could it have been Seo Rin?

37
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:37,430
Did Seo Rin do that
knowing about Professor Kang and me?

38
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:41,430
Is that why she's refusing
to marry General Manager Kang?

39
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:48,440
I have so much to tell you, Baek Ho.

40
00:02:49,110 --> 00:02:52,310
It's okay. Tell me everything.
Tell me exactly what happened.

41
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:55,910
I don't know where to start.

42
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,550
Seo Rin and I...

43
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:04,390
are twins.

44
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:08,360
That explains it. So you're twins.

45
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:09,760
Yes.

46
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:12,100
But there's something even more shocking.

47
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:15,070
The person who hit Seo Rin and me
with that truck...

48
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:17,540
was a henchman sent by Chae Hwa Young.

49
00:03:17,670 --> 00:03:18,670
What?

50
00:03:19,370 --> 00:03:20,970
You're saying CEO Chae did that?

51
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,340
I know it's hard to believe.

52
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,010
You don't know the first thing
about Chae Hwa Young.

53
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:30,350
My mom's accident, my dad's death,

54
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:33,380
and the reason Seo Rin and I
were separated despite being twins...

55
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:35,520
Chae Hwa Young was...

56
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:37,290
behind all of it.

57
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:41,530
Then CEO Chae must have been the one
trying to kill you all along.

58
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:44,630
Yes. If it got out that we're twins,

59
00:03:44,930 --> 00:03:48,100
Chairman Ma would find out
that she'd kidnapped Seo Rin.

60
00:03:48,730 --> 00:03:51,300
She couldn't risk being exposed
as a child kidnapper,

61
00:03:51,770 --> 00:03:53,770
so she was determined
to get rid of me, no matter what.

62
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:57,610
She wanted me gone from this world.

63
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,640
That's unbelievable.

64
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:04,480
And that's how Director Ma
ended up taking your place.

65
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,820
Seriously, how could she do
something so despicable?

66
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:13,660
It wasn't enough that she kidnapped
your twin, Seo Rin.

67
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:17,400
She put the very child she raised
for 30 years into a coma.

68
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,130
Chae Hwa Young isn't even human.

69
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,970
I'll never forgive her.

70
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:24,600
So, after you learned the truth,

71
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:27,740
you decided to take Director Ma's place
in that house.

72
00:04:28,010 --> 00:04:29,510
To get your revenge on Chae Hwa Young.

73
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:30,840
Yes.

74
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:35,510
To make Chae Hwa Young pay for her crimes,
I need conclusive evidence.

75
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:37,850
And to find that evidence,

76
00:04:39,050 --> 00:04:41,350
I had no choice
but to impersonate Ma Seo Rin.

77
00:04:42,090 --> 00:04:45,020
You must have been so anxious
and scared all this time.

78
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:49,790
Footage of Chae Hwa Young
harming your father...

79
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,330
would be the smoking gun.

80
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:53,500
We have to find it, no matter what.

81
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:57,500
Yes. And proof of what
she did to my mother, too.

82
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:00,470
Looks like we have
a lot of work ahead of us.

83
00:05:01,540 --> 00:05:04,440
No. This is something I have to do alone.

84
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:07,580
The reason I stayed away
from you until now...

85
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:11,380
is that I didn't want to
drag you into this mess.

86
00:05:11,450 --> 00:05:13,380
How could you say that?

87
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:16,620
Finding evidence for what happened
to your father is my fight too.

88
00:05:16,690 --> 00:05:18,460
Baek Ho, are you still here?

89
00:05:22,730 --> 00:05:26,330
I'm so sorry.
I didn't realize you had company.

90
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:29,330
Hello.

91
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:32,170
Mom, you were home just a while ago.
What are you doing here?

92
00:05:34,140 --> 00:05:36,810
I forgot some files for tomorrow's trial.

93
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:47,750
Is Seo Rin home yet?

94
00:05:48,090 --> 00:05:50,250
- Not yet.
- But her car is parked outside.

95
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,460
Where could she have gone without driving?

96
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,590
The Chairman said he wanted to see you
as soon as you got in.

97
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:57,430
Father did?

98
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,400
But...

99
00:06:00,930 --> 00:06:02,730
what brings you here so late at night?

100
00:06:02,730 --> 00:06:03,800
Oh, right.

101
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:07,540
Hello, I'm Ma Seo Rin.

102
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:11,910
I'm here for some legal advice
from Lawyer Kang.

103
00:06:12,340 --> 00:06:14,550
Hey, you said you had a trial tomorrow.
You should get going.

104
00:06:16,980 --> 00:06:18,650
Sorry about that.

105
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:33,930
What do you mean,
General Manager Kang Jun Ho is...

106
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:35,470
out of the question?

107
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:38,800
I'm saying he is not a suitable match
for our Seo Rin.

108
00:06:39,370 --> 00:06:40,570
Absolutely not.

109
00:06:40,910 --> 00:06:45,340
Of all the men in the world,
you pick one of our employees for her?

110
00:06:46,610 --> 00:06:49,750
Father, I've put in a lot of thought
about this.

111
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:51,020
You thought a lot about this?

112
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:55,050
Who do you think you are
to decide who Seo Rin marries?

113
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:57,620
I'll find a suitable husband for Seo Rin.

114
00:06:57,690 --> 00:07:00,190
You stay out of it.

115
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:04,500
Father, I know Seo Rin best.

116
00:07:04,730 --> 00:07:08,770
I'm her mother.
Who could know her better than I do?

117
00:07:08,830 --> 00:07:09,830
So?

118
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,070
Are you saying that I, her grandfather,

119
00:07:12,770 --> 00:07:14,840
don't know a thing about her?

120
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:16,410
That's not what I meant.

121
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:20,010
Seo Rin is in love
with General Manager Kang.

122
00:07:20,910 --> 00:07:22,510
She's just throwing a tantrum...

123
00:07:22,710 --> 00:07:25,550
and taking it out on him
due to the accident.

124
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:28,290
If you don't let her marry
General Manager Kang,

125
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:30,720
she won't want to stay in Korea.

126
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:37,160
Seo Rin isn't a child.

127
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:40,130
Let's give it some time
and see what happens.

128
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:45,200
Honey, while you're looking for
a match for Seo Rin,

129
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:47,970
could you please find one
for our Hong Ju, too?

130
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,280
- I should get going.
- Jang Mi.

131
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:03,350
Don't do anything dangerous on your own.
Let me handle it.

132
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:05,790
You need to go back to your old life.

133
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:09,330
You'll be found out in no time,
living in Chairman Ma's house.

134
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:10,390
No.

135
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,800
I can't go back to my old life
until I see this through...

136
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,500
with Chae Hwa Young.

137
00:08:14,570 --> 00:08:17,440
If you're caught, you could get hurt!

138
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:18,870
I'll be careful.

139
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:20,170
Don't worry about me.

140
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,820
Ma Seo Rin, you're finally home.

141
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,360
Were you out with Jun Ho?

142
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,390
But is something wrong?

143
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:44,730
What's this?

144
00:08:44,730 --> 00:08:46,860
You were a drunken mess earlier,
but now you're fine?

145
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:50,030
You couldn't even stand up
and had to be carried in by a guy.

146
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,440
You saw that?

147
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,040
You saw my Baek Ho?

148
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,940
Isn't he gorgeous?

149
00:08:57,810 --> 00:08:59,210
He's cute, I guess.

150
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,450
What's all the fuss about?

151
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:03,920
Listen to you. "Cute, I guess?"

152
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:06,720
Open your eyes. He looks like he jumped
right off the page of a comic book.

153
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:08,320
A man straight out of a comic book.

154
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,920
Beauty is in the eye of the beholder.

155
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,160
But why are you so desperate?

156
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,360
Did you really have to pretend
to be that drunk and stick to him?

157
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:16,790
I get it now.

158
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:18,430
He's not falling for you,

159
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:19,830
so you had to resort to a sly trick
like that, right?

160
00:09:19,830 --> 00:09:20,830
Ma Seo Rin.

161
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:25,000
Come to think of it,
I bet you look upset...

162
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,570
because of Jun Ho, right?

163
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:29,840
Why? Is it not working out
with Jun Ho these days?

164
00:09:29,970 --> 00:09:31,310
Mind your own business.

165
00:09:31,610 --> 00:09:33,140
And stop making such a fool of yourself.

166
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:37,250
What's with her?

167
00:09:38,380 --> 00:09:40,620
She's back to her usual bratty self.

168
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:43,720
Is her memory starting to come back?

169
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:55,270
Thank goodness.
I'm so glad Jang Mi is safe.

170
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,370
Wait, so the person I've been visiting,

171
00:09:58,370 --> 00:10:00,470
holding hands and talking with daily,

172
00:10:00,810 --> 00:10:02,310
was Director Ma Seo Rin this whole time?

173
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:05,480
Jang Mi, I'm right here.

174
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:07,510
You can hear my voice, right?

175
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,510
Every time I wanted to see
Director Ma Seo Rin,

176
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:11,920
something always got in the way.

177
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:13,580
It was because of CEO Chae.

178
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,170
I don't know who you are,

179
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:32,100
but why did you send me a photo
of CEO Chae and Professor Kang...

180
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,900
and tell me not to trust CEO Chae?

181
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,110
Can we meet and talk in person?

182
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,850
First, I'll meet with Baek Ho tomorrow.

183
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:51,860
Then I need to see Tae Pyung.

184
00:10:58,060 --> 00:11:00,400
The common enemy
we must defeat together...

185
00:11:00,730 --> 00:11:02,470
is now Chae Hwa Young.

186
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:05,940
I'll be in touch.
We'll be able to meet soon.

187
00:11:06,170 --> 00:11:07,240
A common enemy?

188
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:10,670
CEO Chae is our common enemy?

189
00:11:12,140 --> 00:11:13,210
That's ridiculous.

190
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:16,050
What in the world is this mystery?

191
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,350
Hey, Baek Ho.

192
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,520
Hey, Tae Pyung.

193
00:11:24,190 --> 00:11:25,960
Jang Mi is doing fine
at the hospital, right?

194
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:29,430
What are you talking about?
Of course she is.

195
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:33,160
I was just checking, just in case.

196
00:11:34,530 --> 00:11:36,000
Sorry to call so late. Get some sleep.

197
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,010
That was so random of Baek Ho.

198
00:11:42,170 --> 00:11:44,480
Anyway, his love for her is so pure.

199
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:49,350
I should probably tell
Tae Pyung the truth.

200
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:53,180
But I should probably leave that
up to Jang Mi, right?

201
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:04,960
By the way, where did you go
with your car parked...

202
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,230
in front of the house?

203
00:12:06,830 --> 00:12:08,670
Do I have to report my every move
to you at my age?

204
00:12:09,330 --> 00:12:11,670
- Why are you being so suffocating?
- Ma Seo Rin.

205
00:12:12,270 --> 00:12:14,310
You only play the adult
when it's convenient for you, don't you?

206
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:18,410
From the look on your face,
you didn't sleep well again.

207
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:21,650
Try not to rely on sleeping pills.

208
00:12:22,350 --> 00:12:24,180
Here, drink this. It's freshly made.

209
00:12:25,050 --> 00:12:27,120
Just leave it there.
I'll drink it after I wash up.

210
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:37,060
You honestly...

211
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,660
don't remember
General Manager Kang Jun Ho?

212
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:41,370
Am I supposed to?

213
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:45,740
You're the one who begged me to marry him,
saying he was the only one.

214
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:48,010
So I gave in
and began to seriously consider...

215
00:12:48,010 --> 00:12:50,670
Director Kang Jun Ho for you.

216
00:12:51,180 --> 00:12:53,140
So if you say that you don't remember now,

217
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,810
- where does that leave me?
- I don't know.

218
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:58,280
What do you want me to do
if I can't remember?

219
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:01,750
You can forget everything else,
but you have to remember Kang Jun Ho.

220
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:04,120
This just won't do.

221
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:06,290
I'm going to have to call Dr. Kim.

222
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:07,560
Actually,

223
00:13:07,990 --> 00:13:09,590
- I remember.
- You do?

224
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:11,500
I knew you did.

225
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,030
Then why were you pretending you didn't?

226
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,370
Because I've lost interest.

227
00:13:17,970 --> 00:13:20,270
- What?
- People change.

228
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,770
Did you expect me
to stay devoted to him forever?

229
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,870
If I'm not interested,
I'm not getting married.

230
00:13:25,380 --> 00:13:26,480
But Mom,

231
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:29,910
why are you so set on me
marrying General Manager Kang Jun Ho?

232
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,320
That's...

233
00:13:33,380 --> 00:13:36,490
That's because you liked Kang Jun Ho...

234
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,660
and you begged me to let you marry him.

235
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:41,060
Like I said, I don't like him anymore.

236
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:45,130
- And that's why I'm not marrying him.
- And that's what's so strange.

237
00:13:45,530 --> 00:13:47,600
Why are you suddenly acting
like a completely different person?

238
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:49,370
No way.

239
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,670
She lost interest in Jun Ho,

240
00:13:52,170 --> 00:13:53,470
so she's not going to marry him?

241
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:05,050
Jun Ho, you're working
with Director Ma, right?

242
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:07,050
Yes.

243
00:14:07,620 --> 00:14:08,950
- Why?
- Why did...

244
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:12,090
Director Ma come to see you
so late last night?

245
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,060
Was it really for some legal advice?

246
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:15,730
Director Ma came to see you?

247
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:18,630
- Yes, something like that.
- And?

248
00:14:19,530 --> 00:14:20,600
What happened?

249
00:14:21,130 --> 00:14:23,170
You've been dying to meet
Director Ma, haven't you?

250
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:24,470
You did?

251
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:28,370
It'll be a problem
if you become interested in her, Baek Ho.

252
00:14:28,810 --> 00:14:31,040
Especially since CEO Chae is trying
to set her up with Jun Ho for marriage.

253
00:14:31,110 --> 00:14:33,880
What's this about a marriage?
That's absolute nonsense!

254
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:36,480
Goodness.

255
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,180
It will only happen
if Jun Ho actually wants...

256
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:40,080
to marry CEO Chae's daughter,

257
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:42,150
but is that any reason to get so angry?

258
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:45,860
What's gotten into you?

259
00:14:46,820 --> 00:14:49,430
I mean, Jun Ho isn't interested.

260
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:52,100
Why do you keep pushing him
to be with Director Ma?

261
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,300
That's why I'm so upset.

262
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:55,470
You never know with these things.

263
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:58,240
Besides, I hear they're working together.

264
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,440
And from what I saw yesterday,
Ma Seo Rin...

265
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:02,670
seemed so graceful and polite.

266
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:05,480
- She seemed like a good catch.
- Graceful?

267
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,540
And you think she's polite?

268
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:09,310
Hey, can I talk to you for a second?

269
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:21,690
You're not really thinking about
marrying Director Ma, are you?

270
00:15:22,090 --> 00:15:23,190
You're not interested in her, right?

271
00:15:24,430 --> 00:15:25,700
Why do I have to tell you that?

272
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:27,500
What's that supposed to mean?

273
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:29,900
Are you saying
you've had a change of heart?

274
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:31,270
Who knows.

275
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:35,340
Why do you care if things work out
between Director Ma and me?

276
00:15:36,010 --> 00:15:37,110
I'm just...

277
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:40,280
- curious.
- And why would you be curious?

278
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:43,650
You were all for me
marrying Director Ma before.

279
00:15:44,380 --> 00:15:45,380
Don't tell me...

280
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,920
you've developed feelings for her...

281
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:50,450
after meeting her once.

282
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:52,490
What? That's ridiculous.

283
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:55,530
I was just curious, that's all.

284
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,850
What is going on here?

285
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:21,420
Who got rid of Team Leader Jin's desk?

286
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:23,820
Director Ma, did you do this?

287
00:16:23,890 --> 00:16:26,090
Why would I waste my energy
on something so petty?

288
00:16:27,930 --> 00:16:29,790
- Then...
- So this is...

289
00:16:29,790 --> 00:16:32,060
the desk disappearing act
I've heard about.

290
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:35,630
You're really in the hot seat now,
Team Leader Jin.

291
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:39,400
CEO Chae, are you really doing this to me?

292
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,710
Just as I thought.

293
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:44,440
Chae Hwa Young suspected
Hong Ju and decided to lower the boom.

294
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:51,650
Ma'am, my desk is gone,

295
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,720
and I just don't understand why.

296
00:16:54,050 --> 00:16:55,950
All I've done is work my hardest.

297
00:16:56,950 --> 00:16:59,320
Your desk? Your desk is gone?

298
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:03,560
I guess you can't work today, then.

299
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,000
Ma'am...

300
00:17:06,060 --> 00:17:10,600
A lot of companies are hot-desking now.
People just find a spot with their laptop.

301
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:14,170
Just grab your laptop and work at a table.

302
00:17:14,370 --> 00:17:15,410
How could I...

303
00:17:16,110 --> 00:17:18,210
Everyone else has their own desk.

304
00:17:18,780 --> 00:17:21,010
How could I be the only one?
It's humiliating.

305
00:17:21,010 --> 00:17:22,910
Team Leader Jin, this is a company.

306
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:25,820
Crying and throwing a fit
won't change a thing.

307
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:29,150
You must have done something
to deserve it.

308
00:17:29,490 --> 00:17:30,490
Don't you think?

309
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:32,820
Now, get out.

310
00:17:33,090 --> 00:17:34,830
If you don't want to work,
feel free to go home.

311
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:39,030
That won't be necessary.

312
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,870
I can't quit this job.

313
00:17:42,730 --> 00:17:45,970
I'll write a formal apology
for my wrongdoing. So please...

314
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:48,670
That's enough.
Didn't you hear me? I said to get out.

315
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:55,480
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

316
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:03,720
What?

317
00:18:03,990 --> 00:18:06,590
Hwa Young took away your desk?

318
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:07,790
Yes.

319
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:09,560
What am I going to do now?

320
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:14,160
What did you do to make that witch
get personal revenge on you like this?

321
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:16,370
I sent that bouquet and pretended
it was from Professor Kang.

322
00:18:17,170 --> 00:18:20,300
- She found out, so this is her revenge.
- So?

323
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:23,670
Why is she being so petty
over something so insignificant?

324
00:18:24,710 --> 00:18:26,280
And to my precious daughter,
of all people.

325
00:18:26,910 --> 00:18:28,080
That Chae Hwa Young. I ought to...

326
00:18:29,850 --> 00:18:33,220
- I'm so furious.
- What are you so furious about?

327
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,120
Hong Ju, let me call you back.

328
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:40,190
Honey. I mean, Mr. Chairman.

329
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:42,230
Have you ever heard of anything so unfair?

330
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,160
What is it now?

331
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:47,400
CEO Chae took away Hong Ju's desk.

332
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:51,440
What else could this be
but a threat to make her quit?

333
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:54,400
So how can I not be furious?

334
00:18:55,610 --> 00:18:57,410
They took her desk away at work?

335
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:59,840
Why would CEO Chae do that?

336
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:04,410
- There must have been a reason.
- It's because of the bouquet...

337
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:06,350
What?

338
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:08,550
Nothing.

339
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:13,360
From now on, don't bother me
with these petty issues.

340
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,190
I've already got enough
on my plate with work.

341
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:27,770
Tae Sook, you're always great at work.
You'll do great with your own business.

342
00:19:28,970 --> 00:19:31,840
We've gotten so many more customers
since you've been here.

343
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,780
Thank you for saying so, sir.

344
00:19:35,450 --> 00:19:36,580
The contract's signed.

345
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:38,550
I'll make sure there are no delays...

346
00:19:38,550 --> 00:19:40,050
on the final payment
as per the date on the contract.

347
00:19:40,050 --> 00:19:41,080
Please do.

348
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:46,590
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

349
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:05,040
Hello?

350
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,280
Baek Ho.

351
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:07,840
It's me.

352
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:12,920
Yes, Jang Mi.

353
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:15,720
- Did you get home okay yesterday?
- Yes.

354
00:20:17,020 --> 00:20:19,760
It's been a while since we've talked
on the phone like this.

355
00:20:20,390 --> 00:20:21,390
It really has.

356
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:23,460
I still can't believe it.

357
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:25,900
I couldn't sleep a wink last night.

358
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:30,070
Just thinking about you fighting all alone
in that strange, dangerous house.

359
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:33,300
Where are you?

360
00:20:33,740 --> 00:20:35,670
I'm at the side dish shop.

361
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:37,670
There was some paperwork
I needed to file with the city.

362
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:39,440
Thank you.

363
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:42,210
Don't you worry about
things here, Jang Mi.

364
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:45,880
I'm here every day, clocking in
and looking after your mom.

365
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:47,880
Jang Mi?

366
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:52,460
- Tae Pyung?
- Hey, Kang Baek Ho.

367
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:55,030
Who are you on the phone with?

368
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:02,070
Are you really...

369
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:04,270
my sister, Jang Mi?

370
00:21:05,370 --> 00:21:06,470
Are you really Oh Jang Mi?

371
00:21:08,470 --> 00:21:09,540
Yes, Tae Pyung.

372
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:13,340
It's me. Your sister, Jang Mi.

373
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,110
You...

374
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:18,580
You little brat...

375
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:22,850
When did you wake up?

376
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:26,160
You should have called me
the second you woke up!

377
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:27,790
I'm sorry, Tae Pyung.

378
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:30,360
Do you have any idea how worried I was?

379
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,700
I thought you might never wake up.

380
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:34,970
I was so...

381
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:37,870
Tae Pyung.

382
00:21:39,070 --> 00:21:41,540
Tae Pyung, I'm so sorry.

383
00:21:44,170 --> 00:21:46,610
But the person lying
in that hospital bed right now...

384
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:48,780
isn't me.

385
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:51,150
What are you talking about?

386
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,450
The person lying in that hospital bed...

387
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:55,550
isn't me.

388
00:21:56,150 --> 00:21:57,290
It's Ma Seo Rin.

389
00:21:58,420 --> 00:21:59,920
She's my twin sister.

390
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:02,060
My little sister.

391
00:22:03,290 --> 00:22:04,490
A twin?

392
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,860
What kind of crazy talk is this?

393
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,670
She's telling the truth, Tae Pyung.

394
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:24,150
So that's the kind of person
CEO Chae really is?

395
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:27,420
She pretended to help our family,
but she's the one who did that to our dad?

396
00:22:28,150 --> 00:22:30,290
Hey. I get how you feel,

397
00:22:30,550 --> 00:22:31,690
but you need to calm down first.

398
00:22:31,690 --> 00:22:34,190
Baek Ho. I'm sorry about back then.

399
00:22:34,690 --> 00:22:36,590
I honestly thought it was
Professor Kang...

400
00:22:40,430 --> 00:22:41,470
Wait a minute.

401
00:22:42,330 --> 00:22:44,200
Professor Kang and CEO Chae...

402
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:45,800
Tae Pyung.

403
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:48,370
Wait, what is it?

404
00:22:49,070 --> 00:22:50,840
Am I the only one who's out of the loop?

405
00:22:51,110 --> 00:22:52,640
No, it's not like that.

406
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:56,450
Seriously, what nonsense is this?

407
00:22:56,550 --> 00:22:59,720
Don't tell anyone
I'm posing as Ma Seo Rin.

408
00:23:00,150 --> 00:23:03,790
Until I make Chae Hwa Young pay,
nobody can know who I really am.

409
00:23:03,850 --> 00:23:06,590
Of course. It would be too dangerous
for you, Jang Mi.

410
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:09,960
Alright, I get it. My lips are sealed.

411
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:12,000
Chae Hwa Young, that woman...

412
00:23:13,730 --> 00:23:15,070
I won't let her get away with this.

413
00:23:15,170 --> 00:23:17,830
See? This is exactly why
I couldn't tell anyone.

414
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:18,900
Don't worry.

415
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:22,870
But...

416
00:23:23,710 --> 00:23:25,210
Don't you miss Mom?

417
00:23:26,540 --> 00:23:27,610
Of course I do.

418
00:23:28,510 --> 00:23:29,750
How's she doing?

419
00:23:30,410 --> 00:23:31,920
She must be asking for me a lot, right?

420
00:23:32,780 --> 00:23:35,720
She's doing a lot better
than she was at first, though.

421
00:23:39,260 --> 00:23:41,790
Bo Ra loves rolled omelets.

422
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:47,900
It's yummy. Bo Ra loves rolled omelets.

423
00:23:48,030 --> 00:23:49,530
Bo Ra loves Grandma.

424
00:23:50,330 --> 00:23:53,000
I like Bo Ra. Bo Ra is pretty.

425
00:23:56,410 --> 00:23:58,710
I miss Jang Mi.

426
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,170
(Ian Daily News)

427
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:30,640
(Restructuring on Three Pillars,
Tourism and Lifestyle...)

428
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:32,540
(The Female Leader
Women Most Aspire to Be...)

429
00:24:32,610 --> 00:24:33,880
(is CEO Chae Hwa Young of Dream Hotel)

430
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:37,910
(With K-culture's spread,
evolving into a K-culture destination...)

431
00:24:38,420 --> 00:24:39,520
("K-culture" and "Polarization")

432
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:11,480
(Chae Hwa Young)

433
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:18,690
(Copying one item
from Desktop to New Folder...)

434
00:25:27,300 --> 00:25:29,270
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

435
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:32,940
Kang Jun Ho.

436
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:35,940
You couldn't stand Director Ma,
thinking she was a stalker.

437
00:25:36,710 --> 00:25:39,740
So why are you so upset
now that she says she dislikes you?

438
00:25:45,250 --> 00:25:46,850
Hello, this is Kang Jun Ho.

439
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:51,520
General Manager Kang.

440
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:54,560
I'd like to formally invite you
to my home.

441
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:57,190
- What do you say?
- What's the occasion?

442
00:25:57,560 --> 00:26:00,330
Let's say it's to wish
the Dream Project success?

443
00:26:01,030 --> 00:26:03,330
Sounds like you sent the invitation first
and are making up the reason now.

444
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:07,170
And what if I did?
This is all for your sake.

445
00:26:08,340 --> 00:26:09,970
Stop it. You're making him uncomfortable.

446
00:26:11,370 --> 00:26:13,980
I accept. How about sometime this weekend?

447
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:17,080
First the father, now the son?
Doesn't that seem a little strange?

448
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,480
I don't know about this.

449
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:21,950
Mom, why are you so set on inviting him?

450
00:26:30,730 --> 00:26:32,500
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

451
00:26:36,170 --> 00:26:39,370
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

452
00:26:55,450 --> 00:26:56,690
I should get going.

453
00:26:58,050 --> 00:26:59,190
Aren't you leaving, Director Ma?

454
00:27:00,090 --> 00:27:02,790
You go ahead.
I have something to discuss with my mom.

455
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:05,000
All right, then.

456
00:27:19,980 --> 00:27:22,710
I thought you were done talking
when I saw the General Manager leaving.

457
00:27:29,950 --> 00:27:30,950
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

458
00:27:33,260 --> 00:27:34,690
You're pretty slick.

459
00:27:35,430 --> 00:27:37,260
You used to just throw yourself at him,

460
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:40,960
but now you know how to pull back
and let him come to you.

461
00:27:41,770 --> 00:27:42,900
I know what I'm doing, Mom.

462
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:46,470
Who sent this?

463
00:27:54,380 --> 00:27:55,580
Gosh, why won't this open?

464
00:28:30,350 --> 00:28:32,650
Who is this?

465
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:54,600
(The First Man)

466
00:28:54,670 --> 00:28:57,310
I don't know who it is,

467
00:28:57,310 --> 00:28:58,810
but I think CEO Chae is being blackmailed.

468
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:01,610
- Blackmailed?
- We have to find that USB.

469
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:04,180
It could be the crucial evidence
from my dad's accident.

470
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:07,150
I'll find it no matter what
and make her pay.

471
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:12,090
CEO Chae Hwa Young,
I trust you received the gift I sent.

472
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:14,990
Who are you?
How dare you pull a stunt like this?

473
00:29:17,930 --> 00:29:19,830
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
